File: Tshwane mayor Randall Williams. eNCA PRETORIA - Randall Williams has resigned as mayor of Tshwane. Williams said he’s resigning to ensure the stability of the multi-party coalition. "I do not want the political instability that has taken place in Johannesburg and Ekurhuleni to spill over into Tshwane," Williams said in a statement. READ: We inherited a bankrupt metro: Tshwane coalition government "To keep the multi-party coalition together required continuous communication and engagement to ensure unity in our city to achieve our goals." DA leaders John Steenhuisen and Solly Msimang thanked Williams for his service.